---
import DocsLayout from "../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout title="Introduction">
    <article class="docs-content">
        <h1>Documentation</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-400 mb-8">
            Welcome to the Gabay documentation. Gabay is an agentic AI designed
            to be actually easy to navigate and integrate into your daily
            workflow.
        </p>

        <h2 id="quick-start">Quick Start</h2>
        <p>
            Getting started with Gabay is straightforward. You can use our CLI
            tool or integrate the agent directly into your application using our
            SDK.
        </p>
        <pre><code>npm install @gabay/core</code></pre>

        <h2 id="installation">Installation</h2>
        <p>To install the Gabay environment locally, follow these steps:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Ensure you have <strong>Node.js 18+</strong> installed.</li>
            <li>Clone the repository or install via npm.</li>
            <li>
                Configure your environment variables in a <code>.env</code> file.
            </li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="architecture">Core Architecture</h2>
        <p>
            Gabay is built on a modular architecture that separates the <strong
                >Agent Logic</strong
            >, <strong>Context Memory</strong>, and <strong
                >Interface Layout</strong
            >.
        </p>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-10">
            <div class="bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-lg p-6">
                <h4 class="text-blue-500 font-bold mb-2">The Brain</h4>
                <p class="text-sm">
                    Processes natural language and determines the optimal
                    sequence of tool calls.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-lg p-6">
                <h4 class="text-blue-500 font-bold mb-2">The Memory</h4>
                <p class="text-sm">
                    Maintains persistent state across conversations using a
                    vector-based storage system.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <h3>Configuration</h3>
        <p>
            You can customize the agent behavior by modifying the <code
                >gabay.config.json</code
            > file at the root of your project.
        </p>
        <pre><code>{`{
  "model": "gabay-ultra-v1",
  "temperature": 0.7,
  "max_context_tokens": 8192,
  "features": {
    "web_browsing": true,
    "code_execution": true
  }
}`}</code></pre>
    </article>
</DocsLayout>
